dependencies install:
local: --> npm i <modulename>
global --> npm i <modulename> -g   <-- g- global
Ex: <module nme> --> http/express

dependencies uninstall: 
_______________________
once install the module, we can uninstall the modules.
syntax:
 npm uninstall <module nme>
 
 Ex: npm uninstal express
 
check the libraries list
________________________
npm ls  <-- to show up the all the libraries.

search libraries:
____________________
npm search <module name>

Ex: npm search express

node js command line options:
______________________________

1.  node -c : check the syntax check with out executing the code
2.  node -v : version check for node.js
3.  node -h or --help : for help
4.  node -e --> evaluate the values but not print
    Ex: node -e  10 + 10
5.  node -p  --> evaluates the values and print
    Ex: node -p  enter
    > 10 + 10
    20
